HEADWORD: Captainship
<hw>Cap"tain*ship</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The condition,
rank, post, or authority of a captain or chief commander.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧To take the <xex>captainship</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Military skill; <as>as, to show good
<ex>captainship</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Captation</ent>⟦br⟧
